fields.physical_description: Design: chromolithograph on one side with the title and details about the subject and the publisher and advertisement printed on the reverse.
fields.title: Advertising card; France
fields.history_note:
These are more in the line of collecting cards such as the type sold with gum or cigarettes.  They are colourful and designed to be instructive for children.

The cards are numbered and coloured, showing a map of an area of France, a mouse portraying the regional activity and the details of principal towns, industries and farming.  The last few cards represent French protectorates in Africa.  On the reverse is printed: CHARCUTERIE-COMESTIBLES/BIZOUARNE A.
